      "content": "The movement is quite aggressive; because cold air is much denser, it behaves like a solid wall of concrete bulldozing against the warm air shield, forcing it up the slope of the warm air mass. This process requires significant pressure difference to generate the strong winds and rapid lifting often associated with severe thunderstorms. You can visualize it as the cold air undercutting the warm layer, which is why cold fronts are marked by sharper weather changes compared to slower-moving warm fronts.",
